@jackjlli I have created an issue and also changed the message.

Addressed review comments. Added integration tests for realtime LLC (consuming, without consuming), realtime HLC and segment movement stats.

@snleee  brought up a point w.r.t throwing exception on detecting ERROR state in external view.

Currently we throw exception on detecting error in external view. I think it is better to at least discuss the pros and cons of ignoring it and continuing with the hope that probably there is 1 of many segments that is in ERROR state and may be we can continue with rebalancing v/s the current approach of aborting the rebalancer midway by throwing exception.
